&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/cybernetic-postliberalism/texts/how-to-write-a-postliberal-grammar-analysis/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/cybernetic-postliberalism/texts/how-to-write-a-postliberal-grammar-analysis/> ;
  schema:name "How to Write a Postliberal-Grammar Analysis of a Public Discourse" ;
  schema:description "A working procedure for analyzing a public discourse for the rhetorical grammar it deploys: map the moves, test against fascist grammar's six steps, anarchist grammar's six moves, and liberal-inverted grammar; identify the genre figures the grammar deploys, trace the laundering of fascist categories into post-1945 vocabulary, and identify the structural function." ;
